Package cs131.pa1.filter.sequential

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Carrot
    This is the class to pass any results of a command into a file It takes the inputs of any results and prints them into a file created with the object.
    Cat
    Creates a Cat object used to read from files
    CD
    Object to allow the changing of directories
    Error
    Creates an object to allow the returning of errors when commands are not found
    Grep
    An object to allow the searching of a file for lines containing a specific word
    LS
    Object that allows printing the contents of the current directory
    PWD
    Object to give the current working directory for the user.
    SequentialCommandBuilder
    This class manages the parsing and execution of a command.
    SequentialFilter
    An abstract class that extends the Filter and implements the basic functionality of all filters.
    SequentialREPL
    The main implementation of the REPL loop (read-eval-print loop).
    Uniq
    An object to obtain all the unique lines in a file
    WC
    An object to allow the counting of words, lines, and characters in a file.
